[thinking] I’m thinking about using bytecode generation to create a class in the same package that calls `$CallbackInfo.class$`, but it seems like dynamic class loading isn’t an option here. I wonder if MethodHandles with findStatic is the way to go, though I’d have to make sure it runs with `--add-opens`. There’s also a possibility that the source has a class$(String) method instead of class$ in Java 21. It seems like instrumentation might be complicating the MethodHandle invocation. Maybe a new file wasn’t picked up because it’s untracked?
[thinking] 
