[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Reviewing method interception and access**\n\nI’m considering class imports and the method interception signature. It looks like the override can omit the throws clause. When I think about private lookup, it seems a package-private class in a different package may have challenges. PrivateLookupIn requires the target class to be accessible, and it can create a private lookup if the package opens up. I’m recalling that MethodHandles.privateLookupIn needs the caller’s module to open the package. It's interesting to figure out if Native Image might prevent direct access with Class.forName.\n\n**Exploring bytecode generation**\n\nI’m thinking about using bytecode generation to create a class in the same package that calls `$CallbackInfo.class$`, but it seems like dynamic class loading isn’t an option here. I wonder if MethodHandles with findStatic is the way to go, though I’d have to make sure it runs with `--add-opens`. There’s also a possibility that the source has a class$(String) method instead of class$ in Java 21. It seems like instrumentation might be complicating the MethodHandle invocation. Maybe a new file wasn’t picked up because it’s untracked?", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0f9b4183d2d767f90169fa71262920819280344793a28a1bf0\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-nE6LhM3lAXJa4w5BzEx3bf3heBHackV9nf1080TJf2JBmcyKLxSBSRIYvbdc6Fw8SlKD1veC0HLyA6eKeHehbLndMEBEj0fgFnx1YcPJxv53BBVc-YJIqhSA2yz0mLqJ-MsJ4WanU-K9cUO0tTNi0o0xtRMh4eLfRjz01oLZDSJZ-XFSj19DjZBJ7CT8YrUfG4ucKl2wDPDRkKLIeCsoU36R9UHFv8w_mvPJAlk1554Oxdtbhwgya3MBOlXsxE4_JbaKU8CSeJEOHoYFv_8Si5qnVPGNjLTtL3zXw6EB9W7ddv0xLM3wwC9NzIsLqHtYRqI1ldpRJh5NAHNpS-qXKsCoi3_s1V0-rLEY7wWvFcrEgalA0ro4vJTU1fCXBSPE-CpH44vDoRQKgYYR8G3xucBc5mO7k7XMIyC0Z9C5yaRyVG0r4W4o3GWNmV9YE-5-SEHXAtGuIPJXrTrSXyZvojH2gRl_ze0Mola3NgqTwu2nWOfMRBs-PY-d2pnLi1RKLoLLaw87-CFHadJhoxHFgUI6DR2fphRcZ7flyLN13BaWEtdOhm6hYR8Khglv