e. I wonder if MethodHandles with findStatic is the way to go, though I’d have to make sure it runs with `--add-opens`. There’s also a possibility that the source has a class$(String) method instead of class$ in Java 21. It seems like instrumentation might be complicating the MethodHandle invocation. Maybe a new file wasn’t picked up because it’s untracked?\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_XE5hxSEggY0iDfAqtrt3xkyJ|fc_0f9b4183d2d767f90169fa713a34e88192b98e0db7df8e7a48", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0/build/reports/tests/test/classes -name '*CallbackInfo*' -o -name '*InnerCallbackInfo*' -print && grep -R \"InnerCallbackInfo\" -n tests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0/build/reports/tests/test 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 5411, "output": 1187, "cacheRead": 34816, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 41414, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778020643752, "responseId": "resp_0f9b4183d2d767f90169fa7124db908192974d7b82de29d401"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_XE5hxSEggY0iDfAqtrt3xkyJ|fc_0f9b4183d2d767f90169fa713a34e88192b98e0db7df8e7a48", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "tests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0/build/reports/tests/test/packages/com_google_inject.guice.html:131:<a href=\"../classes/com_google_inject.guice.InnerCallbackInfoTest.html\">InnerCallbackInfoTest</a>\ntests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0/build/reports/tests/test/classes/com_google_inject.guice.InnerCallbackInfoTest.html:6:<title>Test results - InnerCallbackInfoTest</title>\ntests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0/build/reports/tests/test/classes/com_google_inject.guice.InnerCallbackInfoTest.html:13:<h1>InnerCallbackInfoTest</h1>\ntests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0/build/reports/tests/test/classes/com_google_inject.guice.Inner